         I find it unusual that nobody has mentioned the fact the Terrorclaw's Hide has mana free Beguile Undead on it... this is awesome! I use it all the time. You can charm mobs mana free and ST and recharm at will... I am killing mobs in The Grey at the temple with this thing using only Dooming Darkness and root (and sometimes a vexing or a slow depending on how the fight is going.) It is also a good test to see if Dire Charm will stick as the level resitriction with Beguile and Dire Charm seems to be the same... and you DON'T wanna waste a Dire Charm and have to wait for it to recycle.</P><P>Galim Grimshade<BR>Warlock of Prexus.<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
