        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Trying to argue the Frog Robe against the Warlock Robe is just stupid.  Frog Robe gives no hit points at all, hit points are our bread and butter.  Not to mention the Warlock Robes stats beat the Frog Robe in all other categories except saves which are useless in such small quantities as what the Frog Robes delivers.</P><P>Saying that the effect is useless when its on your dead corpse is stupid.  That is why we have a spell that takes mana that summons our corpse, and all smart necros keep a few coffins in the bank.  Regardless of where your robe is, youre still dead and you have to run back to the zone to summon your body.</P><P>Back on topic:<BR>8th Shawl owns the Terrorclaw and ODS. Terrorclaw is good, very good.  However, the 8th shawl's stats surpass it, the choice is obvious. FT2 in the shoulder is better than MP3 because you can get the same effect in the neck slot where you dont have to give up as much ( for me 65hp/mana ) from a Crystalline Torque.  Granted the Torque has no other stats aside 12ac and MP3, but there are not a lot of nice quest items out there that you might be wearing in the neck slot either.  Personally, i keep both the 65hp/mana neck and Crystalline Torque on me at all times, swapping them as the need arises.  When I am pumping mana to the mages for CoH/Rods i can continue pumping with the torque equipped far longer than without.  </P><P>And if you think saving 1 - 10% off every cast is meaningless for necros, think about this:  Some of our spells, alot of our spells, have a very large mana cost.  Shaving 5.5% average off every Sedulous is huge.  Shaving 5.5% average off of mind wrack is *cough* HUGE!  And let us not forget our ever faithful Lifetaps, which become much more efficient when cast with a MP3 item equipped.  Bottom line: all things being equal, a necro using MP3 is a more efficient necro.  A more efficient necro is a better necro.</P><P>Vtyn</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border