         I am a big fan of effects and effeciency.  But I think one thing has failed to be mentioned here. Maybe I missed it?</P><P>IF you have an affliction effeciency item (which I HIGHLY recommend for any necro) then the mana preservation does NOT stack when casting spells that are effected by affliction effeciency.  The only reason I say this is that i dont get the ODS message whenever I do get the gem encrusted ring message (Am I wrong here?).</P><P>And in addition to this, since the latest patch virtually all of our combat spells are covered by affliction effeciency (including roots, slows, mezzes).  The only regular use combat spells not covered by affliction effeciency are DDs/lifetaps.</P><P>So that being the case...ODS is only saving you mana for your lifetaps and DDs...</P><P>Now, if you are soloing and doing your job correctly you should NEVER be lifetapping or doing DDs unless you have some sort of emergency. On the other hand, if you are grouping, killing rapidly, and doing your job correctly then you should ONLY be casting DDs for damage. If you are raiding, then it is likely that you will be doing both, because of the retarded ass dot stacking PROBLEM. </P><P>So I have put away my ODS for the most part and opt for terrorclaw's hide.  I pull out the ODS and swap out if I am gonna be leaning heavily on DDs.<BR><img src="http://ourworld.cs.com/bgrmail/zorlak.jpg" border=0></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
