        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Malivar:</P><P>I completly agree with your opinion that the items verrant put these focus effects on is completely senseless...and that it really sucks loosing stats to switch out equipment...But, you are only hurting yourself by refusing to wear these items.</P><P>50 to 100hps is NOT greater than having your bread and butter spells cost 25% less mana PERIOD(for example funeral pyre 337 mana versus 450 not considering specialization and SCM).  It is difficult to describe how well this imrpoves your effeciency...people put forth numbers all the time...But regardless of the numbers...The difference is DRAMATIC.  A necromancer without affliction effeciency3 and SCM3 is a JOKE compared to the powerhouse of one with these tools.  I am not saying they arent good, talented or well equiped...i am just saying...it is impossible for them to cast at the rate of the necro with.  And after all...HPs do not improve your effeciency....they only give you more flexibilty with your how you channel and leach your life away.  And trust me...I know that is very important too.</P><P>I have heard people say that mana effeciency in all its forms isnt important to a necro because we regenerate mana so quickly...I say that is a load of horse shit for this very reason...Can you chain cast your powerful spells and run out of mana? the answer to that question is yes...And if you are good, in the right place with alot of mobs to pull, and the skills to solo multiple enemys as once you can and will run out of mana...even with effeciency items.  Yes we do regen mana fast...but when you add to that a reduction in spell cost it only amplifys that powerful feature of the necromancer....it really multiplies our power in a very powerful way.</P><P>Be stubborn if you wish...I know that it is a natural reaction. I batteled with the same feelings at first but decided to give it a try. I know you dont want to remove that sweet item you worked so hard to get in order to equip an item originally designed for melee that no longer drops in the game...but do it...I promise you it is worth it.</P><P><img src="http://ourworld.cs.com/bgrmail/zorlak.jpg" border=0></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
