         Hah when there is actually a camp that I run out of mana killing at or if there is a mob that I run out of mana while killing, I'll consider a mana reduction item.  Aint happened yet and I am not sure it will happen.  Usualy my spell list is so full of utility spells that I only have one or possibly two real mana drainers in there.  But, with the way I fight, I never run out of mana.  In the time I kill a normal exp mob, I often times gain mana as it is.  Why the hell would I want to be full mana again even faster when it means dropping precious health?  The extra 100 health I get from my shoulders has probably saved my ass 10 times as much as some extra mana would have.</P><P>I really don't sacrifice much killing speed for efficiency, either.  In my normal exp spot, I kill 9-10 mobs in the 15 minute spawn cycle and never have a second of down time and never come close to running out of mana.  As a matter of fact, I don't think I've done a solo exp spot where I've had any downtime since I was in my early 40s.</P><P>I think the only effect I might give up even a weak slot for, would be spell casting haste 3 and possibly affliction haste 3.  I am sure the ods is nice but it's not 100 health nice.  100 health increases the beating I can take by slightly less than 5% and have nice resists.  I mean, how many items give you 5% to anything?  Oh, wait...</P><P><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26159">Reegor</A> Mortees<BR>scaled Warlock<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
